FBIS4-39891 "drsov113_v_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 Lithuania Six New Ministers Appointed Six New Ministers Appointed LD1006101494 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 0900 GMT 10 Jun 94 LD1006101494 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network Lithuanian BFN [Text] Being guided by the Lithuanian Constitution and taking into consideration the presentation by Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius, President Algirdas Brazauskas appointed in his edicts six ministers today: Mindaugas Laurynas Stankevicius was appointed minister of administration reforms and municipal affairs, releasing him of his duties as minister of social insurance. The edict comes into force on 1 July. Bronius Brazauskas was appointed minister of the protection of environment. The edict comes into force on 15 June. Vladislovas Domarkas was appointed minister of education and science. Dainius Trinkunas -- minister of culture; Albertas Vasiliauskas -- minister of forestry; Aleksandras Vasiliauskas -- minister of economy. The edicts as regards these ministers come into force today [10 June].
